<p>In the latest development, Hamas handed over the remains of a deceased captive to the International Committee of the Red Cross, which accompanied the transfer into Israeli-controlled areas and transported the coffin toward Israeli forces on October 27–28, 2025 . The handover comes under a U.S.-brokered ceasefire that took effect on 10 October and obliges Hamas to return all remains of Israeli hostages; Israel has agreed to transfer Palestinian bodies in exchange, a process families and officials are monitoring closely . Israeli authorities are conducting forensic identification on arrival; if confirmed as a captive, officials say the returns would bring the tally of remains handed over to 16 of the 28 people held before the ceasefire .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/4VzMlypyrIIfFRxIUGbFi46dOebfbztbI_tg1js_qM4ZCT12Scvq7w9E8pUv5I7Zi8hVVw59kpeVlM1dtgJrJf172YQW9NXRnM1fYnImVIDJrS8YX9nQTeimrDy_57YONF4NEd99D2FkRzTJS-LFwnO79MYzMMDHF83mTW8jaMcxGv98tXOLqNoNJBLEFLZpKmgh_IEVq1dl7DltVV68_3iwJ8Hq7piJvOhbv7H-j5hS0bcsQKMffvGvUXIjFCdBkLjSX0iwhsdTlmziuJwX_x8' alt='Red Cross transports the body of a deceased hostage handed over by Hamas militants, Gaza City, October 27, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Exchange terms: Under the ceasefire framework, Israel agreed to hand over 15 Palestinian bodies for each Israeli returned, a central mechanic of the bilateral exchange negotiations .</li><li>Families&#x27; demands: Families of the October 7 hostages urged U.S. and Israeli authorities to pause the next phase of the truce until all bodies are returned, citing a slowdown after the earlier releases of living captives .</li><li>Israeli response: The Israeli military said the recovery was staged in Gaza City and that IDF drone footage recorded parts of the operation, and Israel&#x27;s prime minister was set to convene a meeting on possible responses to alleged ceasefire violations .</li><li>Forensic process: Following receipt, coffins are taken to a military ceremony and then to the national forensic institute for identification and confirmation before families are notified .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC): The ICRC acted as a neutral intermediary and accompanied Hamas members into areas under Israeli control to facilitate the search for bodies, helping transport the remains to Israeli forces. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/27/red-cross-accompanies-hamas-in-search-for-bodies-of-israeli-hostages-in-gaza'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Israel / Israeli military (IDF): The IDF said the recovery was staged in Gaza City and that the returned coffin is being worked on for identification; the prime minister planned a meeting on possible responses to alleged ceasefire violations. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-october-28-2025/'>Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>Hamas: Hamas announced it handed over the remains of a captive to the Red Cross under the ceasefire terms and participation of intermediaries. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/hamas-says-it-handed-over-hostages-remains-to-red-cross-israel-working-to-id-body/'>Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>Families of hostages: Families urged U.S. and Israeli authorities to pause the next phase of the truce until all bodies are returned and criticized the slowing pace of transfers. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/hamas-returns-captive-body-families-urge-pause-gaza-truce'>New Arab</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/27/red-cross-accompanies-hamas-in-search-for-bodies-of-israeli-hostages-in-gaza'>Hamas returns remains of Israeli hostage after Red Cross’s help in search</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/liveblog-october-28-2025/'>Casket handed over by Hamas believed to contain further remains of previously returned hostage</a> - timesofisrael.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/hamas-returns-captive-body-